00:00:01.001 --> 00:00:03.103 line:5%,start
[music playing] Previously
on "Dance Moms"--

00:00:03.169 --> 00:00:04.404 line:5%,start
- I just want Kelly back.
- I know.

00:00:04.471 --> 00:00:05.472 line:5%,start
That's the plan.

00:00:05.538 --> 00:00:07.073 line:5%,start
Girls, where are you?

00:00:07.707 --> 00:00:09.976 line:5%,start
I'm going to replace the entire team.

00:00:10.377 --> 00:00:11.611 line:5%,start
Melissa, this is Abby.

00:00:11.945 --> 00:00:15.782 line:5%,start
You are losing your mind
if you're gonna jeopardize

00:00:15.849 --> 00:00:16.983 line:5%,start
Maddie and Mackenzie.

00:00:17.050 --> 00:00:18.818 line:5%,start
They're replacing our kids.

00:00:19.486 --> 00:00:20.587 line:5%,start
Well, welcome!

00:00:20.653 --> 00:00:23.189 line:5%,start
- Thank you.
- My new Maddie-- I'm thrilled.

00:00:23.256 --> 00:00:24.824 line:5%,start
MELISSA: Sofia is on top of the pyramid,

00:00:24.891 --> 00:00:26.393 line:5%,start
and she's not even here.

00:00:26.459 --> 00:00:30.797 line:5%,start
ABBY: My next routine
will be a duet with Maddie and Kendall.

00:00:30.864 --> 00:00:32.665 line:5%,start
ABBY (VOICEOVER):
Coming up on "Dance Moms"--

00:00:32.732 --> 00:00:35.969 line:5%,start
I want to make sure that
you're all aware your replacements

00:00:36.036 --> 00:00:37.170 line:5%,start
will be at the competition.

00:00:37.237 --> 00:00:38.805 line:5%,start
GLORIA: They really
like making fun of our kids.

00:00:38.872 --> 00:00:40.440 line:5%,start
[laughs] ABBY: Sorry.

00:00:40.507 --> 00:00:42.909 line:5%,start
Could you quit running up
to the mirror so close?

00:00:42.976 --> 00:00:44.010 line:5%,start
Think!

00:00:44.077 --> 00:00:45.912 line:5%,start
Mackenzie forgets her dance on stage.

00:00:45.979 --> 00:00:46.980 line:5%,start
She goes completely blank.

00:00:47.047 --> 00:00:48.748 line:5%,start
MELISSA: You now what? You risked--

00:00:48.815 --> 00:00:51.785 line:5%,start
- My daughter is special.
- ABBY: --your kids on Paige and Brooke.

00:00:51.851 --> 00:00:53.119 line:5%,start
You know we all make mistakes, Abby.

00:00:53.186 --> 00:00:54.754 line:5%,start
ABBY: We love you.

00:00:54.821 --> 00:00:57.891 line:5%,start
We were ready to work with you
and you sat out there!

00:00:57.957 --> 00:00:59.793 line:5%,start
I'm sorry.

00:00:59.859 --> 00:01:01.594 line:5%,start
That was hurtful!

00:01:01.661 --> 00:01:03.496 line:95%,end
[theme music]

00:01:03.563 --> 00:01:04.998 line:95%,end
(SINGING) Get up!

00:01:05.065 --> 00:01:07.434 line:95%,end
Get on the floor.

00:01:07.500 --> 00:01:13.807 line:95%,end
My world is with my girls,
living on the dance floor.

00:01:13.873 --> 00:01:16.576 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:01:18.111 --> 00:01:20.647 line:5%,start
GIANNA: Hey, Ab, Devin
just called the studio.

00:01:20.713 --> 00:01:23.016 line:95%,end
Oh, from the competition?
What did he want?

00:01:23.083 --> 00:01:24.717 line:95%,end
He just left a message. I don't know.

00:01:24.784 --> 00:01:28.088 line:95%,end
Hi Devin, this is Abby from
the Abby Lee Dance Company. How are you?

00:01:29.789 --> 00:01:31.291 line:5%,start
ABBY: Good.
I just wanted to return your call.

00:01:31.357 --> 00:01:34.527 line:95%,end
Gianna had said that you called,
and I wanted to thank you.

00:01:51.744 --> 00:01:53.980 line:95%,end
All right.
Well, thank you so much for calling.

00:01:56.015 --> 00:01:58.218 line:95%,end
- How about that?
- So they didn't win.

00:01:58.384 --> 00:02:01.688 line:95%,end
- They did not win.
- Well, Kendall just had a rough weekend.

00:02:01.754 --> 00:02:05.158 line:5%,start
Last week at Dance Troupe
Challenge at Greensboro,

00:02:05.225 --> 00:02:06.559 line:95%,end
Kendall and Maddie won it all.

00:02:06.626 --> 00:02:09.596 line:95%,end
ANNOUNCER: Number 217, "Sugar and Spice,"

00:02:09.662 --> 00:02:11.397 line:95%,end
Abby Lee Dance Company!

00:02:11.464 --> 00:02:12.332 line:95%,end
[cheering and applause]

00:02:12.398 --> 00:02:15.368 line:95%,end
ABBY: Turns out there was an
error in the calculations,

00:02:15.435 --> 00:02:17.403 line:95%,end
and they were second.

00:02:17.470 --> 00:02:20.073 line:95%,end
And we all know what second is--

00:02:20.673 --> 00:02:22.742 line:95%,end
the biggest loser on the stage.

00:02:22.909 --> 00:02:25.645 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:02:31.451 --> 00:02:34.921 line:95%,end
Well, once again, I'm not very happy.

00:02:34.988 --> 00:02:36.422 line:95%,end
When I left that competition,

00:02:36.489 --> 00:02:40.326 line:95%,end
everybody was gloating about
how amazing you were, the big winners.

00:02:40.393 --> 00:02:41.861 line:95%,end
Nothing blew me away.

00:02:41.928 --> 00:02:45.131 line:95%,end
I think all of you would
be interested in knowing

00:02:45.198 --> 00:02:48.401 line:95%,end
that our duet,
"Sugar and Spice," did not win.

00:02:50.937 --> 00:02:53.106 line:95%,end
There was a mathematical error.

00:02:53.706 --> 00:02:56.576 line:95%,end
And that means that "Sugar and Spice,"
Maddie and Kendall,

00:02:56.643 --> 00:02:59.179 line:95%,end
were not the overall
high score winning duet/trio.

00:02:59.345 --> 00:03:01.314 line:95%,end
So Greensboro, North Carolina,

00:03:01.381 --> 00:03:03.483 line:95%,end
which we thought was a smashing success,

00:03:03.550 --> 00:03:04.784 line:95%,end
turned out to be a big letdown.

00:03:04.851 --> 00:03:06.786 line:95%,end
JILL: Abby couldn't wait
to come in and tell us

00:03:06.853 --> 00:03:10.123 line:5%,start
that Kendall and Maddie
did not get first place.

00:03:10.190 --> 00:03:12.625 line:95%,end
And I think Abby reveled in that.

00:03:12.692 --> 00:03:14.093 line:95%,end
I watched the group number.

00:03:14.160 --> 00:03:18.998 line:95%,end
I saw some superb dancing
and I saw some horrendous dancing.

00:03:19.065 --> 00:03:21.501 line:95%,end
Kendall, whose place did you take?

00:03:22.569 --> 00:03:23.703 line:5%,start
ABBY: Sophia's.

00:03:23.770 --> 00:03:25.872 line:95%,end
Did you look like she would
have looked doing that number?

00:03:27.540 --> 00:03:30.476 line:95%,end
You don't know? I'll tell you. No way.


00:03:30.543 --> 00:03:31.945 line:95%,end
Sophia is still in LA.

00:03:32.011 --> 00:03:33.279 line:95%,end
She's there with her mom.

00:03:33.346 --> 00:03:34.480 line:95%,end
She's doing television.

00:03:34.547 --> 00:03:36.149 line:95%,end
She's doing performances.

00:03:36.216 --> 00:03:38.284 line:95%,end
So I need the girls to step
it up in Sophia's absence,

00:03:38.351 --> 00:03:39.652 line:95%,end
and they're just not doing it.

00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:43.189 line:95%,end
Listen to me. Learn this,
every single one of you--

00:03:43.256 --> 00:03:46.459 line:95%,end
when you're in here rehearsing
and you keep screwing up,

00:03:46.526 --> 00:03:51.631 line:95%,end
you don't need me to stand there
and point out every mistake.

00:03:51.698 --> 00:03:52.999 line:95%,end
Can't you see it?

00:03:53.900 --> 00:03:55.501 line:95%,end
If you don't want to be a better dancer,

00:03:55.568 --> 00:03:57.170 line:95%,end
I'm not going to waste my breath on you.

00:03:57.237 --> 00:04:00.273 line:95%,end
I want to worry about the kid
who wants to be a star,

00:04:00.340 --> 00:04:03.876 line:95%,end
not the kid that's here just so she gets
invited to all the birthday parties.

00:04:04.911 --> 00:04:08.047 line:95%,end
Kendall, you worked
your way up that pyramid

00:04:08.114 --> 00:04:10.049 line:95%,end
and now you're right back
where you started from.

00:04:11.684 --> 00:04:13.286 line:95%,end
Next, Maddie.

00:04:13.353 --> 00:04:15.688 line:95%,end
All for one, one for all,
it's about the team.

00:04:15.755 --> 00:04:17.290 line:95%,end
Kendall's there, you went with her.

00:04:19.025 --> 00:04:21.127 line:95%,end
Nia, you did an OK job.

00:04:21.194 --> 00:04:22.996 line:95%,end
I just don't see
the feet getting any better.

00:04:24.797 --> 00:04:29.002 line:95%,end
Moving up, Paige,
you placed in the top five.

00:04:29.068 --> 00:04:30.069 line:95%,end
That's an improvement.

00:04:30.436 --> 00:04:31.304 line:95%,end
Next,

00:04:33.072 --> 00:04:36.276 line:95%,end
Chloe, I thought you really
stood out starting the group dance.

00:04:36.342 --> 00:04:37.844 line:95%,end
Was the group fabulous?

00:04:37.910 --> 00:04:40.847 line:95%,end
No. I think if your mother
was more honest with you,

00:04:40.913 --> 00:04:45.718 line:95%,end
like she used to be two or three years
ago, you would continue to improve.

00:04:46.019 --> 00:04:49.055 line:95%,end
And on top of the pyramid is Mackenzie.

00:04:49.122 --> 00:04:50.923 line:95%,end
[applause]

00:04:52.125 --> 00:04:54.327 line:95%,end
It's like you bumped
your sister right down there.

00:04:54.394 --> 00:04:55.728 line:95%,end
Does it feel good to be up there?

00:04:55.795 --> 00:04:56.796 line:95%,end
Well, guess what?

00:04:57.330 --> 00:04:59.032 line:95%,end
You are back in the group routine.

00:04:59.098 --> 00:05:02.201 line:95%,end
If you could go against 9-year-olds
and win,

00:05:02.268 --> 00:05:03.903 line:95%,end
then you can dance with a 9-year-old.

00:05:03.970 --> 00:05:05.772 line:95%,end
I was the big winner last week,

00:05:05.838 --> 00:05:08.174 line:95%,end
so Abby put me on the top of the pyramid.

00:05:08.241 --> 00:05:10.076 line:5%,start
Pressure's on.

00:05:10.143 --> 00:05:13.880 line:95%,end
This weekend we will be
traveling to In10sity Dance

00:05:13.946 --> 00:05:15.581 line:95%,end
in Woodbridge, Virginia.

00:05:15.648 --> 00:05:18.184 line:95%,end
Your replacements
will be at the competition,

00:05:18.251 --> 00:05:20.186 line:95%,end
along with the rest of their studio.

00:05:20.253 --> 00:05:22.422 line:95%,end
When the moms walked out of my studio,

00:05:23.222 --> 00:05:24.590 line:95%,end
I replaced their kids.

00:05:24.657 --> 00:05:25.591 line:95%,end
That's what you do.

00:05:26.025 --> 00:05:28.594 line:95%,end
Two of those replacements,
Kaeli and Bella,

00:05:28.661 --> 00:05:32.065 line:95%,end
are going to be attending the
dance competition this weekend.

00:05:32.131 --> 00:05:35.034 line:95%,end
And I'm sure that they want nothing more

00:05:35.101 --> 00:05:37.437 line:95%,end
than to beat my team.

00:05:37.770 --> 00:05:39.205 line:95%,end
Mackenzie, you have a solo.

00:05:39.272 --> 00:05:41.974 line:95%,end
Not only are you
in this week's group routine,

00:05:42.041 --> 00:05:44.777 line:95%,end
but you are going to be featured
in the number, as well.

00:05:44.844 --> 00:05:48.514 line:95%,end
That's because this week we
are doing an acrobatic routine.

00:05:49.148 --> 00:05:51.351 line:95%,end
Chloe, I know acrobatics
is not your forte,

00:05:51.517 --> 00:05:52.919 line:95%,end
but your mom has stood at that desk

00:05:52.985 --> 00:05:56.756 line:95%,end
and told me on several occasions
that you have your standing back tuck.

00:05:56.823 --> 00:05:58.391 line:95%,end
So that's how the number
is going to start.

00:05:58.458 --> 00:06:00.193 line:95%,end
- Oh, no. Chloe is not doing a standing--
- ABBY: You're going

00:06:00.259 --> 00:06:01.260 line:95%,end
- to set your tuck.
- Oh, yes, she is.

00:06:01.327 --> 00:06:02.628 line:95%,end
- CHRISTI: No, Abby. I refuse.
- ABBY: Yup.

00:06:02.695 --> 00:06:05.298 line:95%,end
No. Abby, she does not
have permission to do that.

00:06:05.365 --> 00:06:08.134 line:95%,end
- You just said that she had it.
- I said that months ago.

00:06:08.201 --> 00:06:09.736 line:95%,end
Right, so it should be better.

00:06:09.802 --> 00:06:11.804 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Abby telling Chloe
that she's starting the group dance

00:06:11.871 --> 00:06:13.673 line:5%,start
with a standing back
tuck really sets me off.

00:06:13.740 --> 00:06:16.776 line:5%,start
Because Abby knows that Chloe
is not confident in the standing

00:06:16.843 --> 00:06:19.178 line:95%,end
back tuck, so she's really
just setting her up to fail.

00:06:19.245 --> 00:06:21.314 line:95%,end
Chloe, do you think
you're confident enough?

00:06:22.081 --> 00:06:23.282 line:95%,end
Be honest, Chloe.

00:06:23.816 --> 00:06:25.151 line:95%,end
ABBY: Well, why would
you come and tell me your kid

00:06:25.218 --> 00:06:26.319 line:95%,end
- could do a back tuck?
- Because she--

00:06:26.386 --> 00:06:27.987 line:95%,end
When parents come and tell me things,

00:06:28.054 --> 00:06:29.689 line:95%,end
it's because they want me
to work it into the number.

00:06:29.756 --> 00:06:31.657 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: No. Chloe, you are not
doing it in the routine.

00:06:31.724 --> 00:06:34.127 line:95%,end
You know she is afraid
of gymnastics tricks.

00:06:34.193 --> 00:06:36.028 line:95%,end
She is not allowed to do it.

00:06:36.095 --> 00:06:39.031 line:95%,end
You know what? You had Paige do a standing
back in that dressing room

00:06:39.098 --> 00:06:40.299 line:95%,end
- and she broke her foot.
- No, I didn't!

00:06:40.366 --> 00:06:41.267 line:95%,end
Yes, you did!

00:06:41.334 --> 00:06:43.536 line:95%,end
I want to see your standing back tuck.

00:06:43.603 --> 00:06:45.071 line:95%,end
Can I try it?

00:06:45.138 --> 00:06:47.173 line:95%,end
ABBY: No. This is cement
underneath this carpeting.

00:06:47.573 --> 00:06:49.175 line:95%,end
[crunch]

00:06:49.242 --> 00:06:51.611 line:95%,end
You said, "I want to see
that standing back tuck."

00:06:51.677 --> 00:06:53.613 line:95%,end
Chloe, you are not
doing it in the routine.

00:06:53.679 --> 00:06:54.981 line:95%,end
KELLY: But the more we sit here and argue,

00:06:55.047 --> 00:06:57.049 line:95%,end
- the more they're not practicing.
- ABBY: I'm not arguing.

00:06:57.116 --> 00:06:59.886 line:95%,end
I invited a child to do a trick
that her mother said she could do.

00:06:59.952 --> 00:07:02.155 line:95%,end
Chloe, you were supposed
to do a solo this week.


00:07:02.221 --> 00:07:04.824 line:95%,end
But after the performance
your mother just gave,

00:07:04.891 --> 00:07:06.325 line:95%,end
we're going to hold off on that.

00:07:06.392 --> 00:07:07.326 line:95%,end
OK.

00:07:07.393 --> 00:07:09.128 line:95%,end
All right, girls, spread apart.

00:07:09.195 --> 00:07:10.863 line:95%,end
Mothers, you are dismissed.

00:07:10.930 --> 00:07:14.367 line:95%,end
Maybe you want to sit and really watch
upstairs instead of being on your phones.

00:07:14.434 --> 00:07:17.870 line:5%,start
Five, six, seven, eight--

00:07:17.937 --> 00:07:19.038 line:5%,start
I don't even get it.

00:07:19.105 --> 00:07:20.606 line:5%,start
ABBY: One, two--

00:07:21.307 --> 00:07:22.308 line:5%,start
GIANNA: Switch.

00:07:22.442 --> 00:07:25.044 line:95%,end
ABBY: The name of the group
routine is "Arabian Nights."

00:07:25.111 --> 00:07:28.848 line:95%,end
It's a contortion, acrobatic,
gymnastic, tumbling routine.

00:07:28.915 --> 00:07:30.216 line:95%,end
Jump up.

00:07:30.283 --> 00:07:31.751 line:95%,end
You got to jump your feet together.

00:07:31.818 --> 00:07:35.221 line:95%,end
It has it all, complete
with the authentic hands.

00:07:35.288 --> 00:07:37.390 line:95%,end
It has to be sharp, boom.

00:07:37.457 --> 00:07:40.159 line:95%,end
Do you think that I was wrong
for standing up for Chloe?

00:07:40.226 --> 00:07:41.093 line:95%,end
HOLLY: I don't think you're wrong, at all.

00:07:41.160 --> 00:07:43.429 line:95%,end
I just think that you fell
right into Abby's trap.

00:07:43.496 --> 00:07:45.198 line:95%,end
ABBY: One, two--

00:07:45.264 --> 00:07:48.234 line:95%,end
KELLY: I think this Arabian dance
will be a challenge for Paige

00:07:48.301 --> 00:07:51.037 line:95%,end
because Abby always
is yelling at her for her arms.

00:07:51.103 --> 00:07:52.705 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Well, it's gonna
be a challenge for Chloe.

00:07:52.772 --> 00:07:55.174 line:95%,end
Because out of the group,
she's not-- A gymnast.

00:07:55.241 --> 00:07:56.442 line:95%,end
--a gymnast or an acrobat.

00:07:58.211 --> 00:08:00.513 line:95%,end
Paige, your elbows are lazy.

00:08:00.580 --> 00:08:02.114 line:95%,end
First time I'm telling you.

00:08:02.181 --> 00:08:03.416 line:95%,end
Let it be the last.

00:08:03.483 --> 00:08:05.251 line:95%,end
So do you think
that really bothers Maddie,

00:08:05.318 --> 00:08:08.221 line:95%,end
that Kenzie has all these solos
and is the lead?

00:08:08.287 --> 00:08:09.755 line:95%,end
I mean, that's usually Maddie's spot.

00:08:09.822 --> 00:08:12.258 line:95%,end
Yeah, but Maddie
it's not jealous of her sister.

00:08:12.325 --> 00:08:14.093 line:95%,end
She's proud of her.
But she gets stressed out.

00:08:14.160 --> 00:08:17.196 line:95%,end
Melissa, I suggested that
you get some of Christi's spunk

00:08:17.263 --> 00:08:18.865 line:95%,end
that she had at pyramid.

00:08:18.931 --> 00:08:20.600 line:95%,end
I just don't know how you can sit there,

00:08:20.666 --> 00:08:23.369 line:95%,end
like, and not say anything.

00:08:23.436 --> 00:08:26.706 line:95%,end
It's been a few weeks and Maddie
still hasn't had a solo.

00:08:26.772 --> 00:08:30.643 line:95%,end
It's hard. But, you know,
she knows she'll get one eventually.

00:08:31.110 --> 00:08:32.378 line:95%,end
Well, I'm going to talk to Abby.

00:08:32.445 --> 00:08:33.579 line:95%,end
[gasps] You are?

00:08:33.646 --> 00:08:35.481 line:95%,end
- Mm-hmm. Yeah, after--
- HOLLY: Good.

00:08:35.548 --> 00:08:37.283 line:95%,end
- About what?
- After rehearsal.

00:08:37.350 --> 00:08:38.885 line:95%,end
I'm proud of you. That's good.

00:08:38.951 --> 00:08:40.753 line:95%,end
I'm letting you all go. You are dismissed.

00:08:40.820 --> 00:08:42.321 line:95%,end
Go through that door.

00:08:42.388 --> 00:08:44.790 line:95%,end
Ab, can I talk to you
for a sec before you leave?

00:08:44.857 --> 00:08:45.958 line:95%,end
ABBY: Yeah. What?

00:08:46.025 --> 00:08:50.963 line:95%,end
MELISSA: I really would love for Maddie
to prove to you that she can win.

00:08:51.030 --> 00:08:52.131 line:95%,end
- I know, Melissa.
- MELISSA: And, you know--

00:08:52.198 --> 00:08:55.568 line:95%,end
But you have to realize that she was just
in a duet with Kendall.

00:08:55.635 --> 00:08:57.603 line:95%,end
And even though she was
a lot better than Kendall

00:08:57.670 --> 00:08:59.972 line:95%,end
and a lot stronger,
she didn't blow me away, either.

00:09:00.039 --> 00:09:02.508 line:95%,end
She is special.
And my daughter wants to dance.

00:09:02.575 --> 00:09:03.743 line:95%,end
ABBY: I know,
but why am I telling you that?

00:09:03.809 --> 00:09:07.613 line:95%,end
Why wouldn't the kid
that had the potential to make it,

00:09:07.680 --> 00:09:09.549 line:95%,end
to have a career in this business,

00:09:09.615 --> 00:09:13.252 line:95%,end
not have her own integrity,
her own ambition--

00:09:13.319 --> 00:09:15.021 line:95%,end
MELISSA: She wanted to come in.
--to get out of the car and walk in?

00:09:15.087 --> 00:09:16.756 line:95%,end
- She wanted to come. You're not--
- Then why didn't you-- why--

00:09:16.822 --> 00:09:18.324 line:95%,end
what kind of parent were you
