00:18:08.387 --> 00:18:10.089 line:95%,end
We got home so late last night.

00:18:10.255 --> 00:18:13.058 line:95%,end
I got home later because Maddie talked
to Abby last night.

00:18:13.125 --> 00:18:14.526 line:95%,end
JILL: What happened?

00:18:14.593 --> 00:18:16.895 line:95%,end
Her and Abby talked and Abby cried.

00:18:16.962 --> 00:18:18.163 line:95%,end
JILL: Why would Abby cry?

00:18:18.230 --> 00:18:19.798 line:95%,end
MELISSA: Because that
Maddie was crying and saying,

00:18:19.865 --> 00:18:22.167 line:95%,end
you know, you're mad at me
for something my mother did

00:18:22.234 --> 00:18:24.736 line:95%,end
and you do-- you know,
basically she does it to all the kids.

00:18:24.803 --> 00:18:27.539 line:95%,end
Abby said, I love you and Gia loves you.

00:18:27.606 --> 00:18:29.875 line:95%,end
And, you know,
we were just really disappointed

00:18:29.942 --> 00:18:31.577 line:95%,end
in your mom and the decision she made.

00:18:31.643 --> 00:18:32.644 line:95%,end
And--

00:18:32.711 --> 00:18:34.913 line:95%,end
Isn't that a difference
in the conversation?

00:18:34.980 --> 00:18:37.549 line:95%,end
Because she sat there
and cried and had a nice moment

00:18:37.616 --> 00:18:39.384 line:95%,end
with your daughter, where my daughter

00:18:39.451 --> 00:18:41.453 line:95%,end
as she sat there last night, same thing,

00:18:41.520 --> 00:18:43.255 line:95%,end
and pretty much told her
that she was a piece of garbage

00:18:43.322 --> 00:18:45.124 line:95%,end
and didn't deserve to have anything.

00:18:45.991 --> 00:18:47.126 line:95%,end
I mean, I'm glad for you.

00:18:47.192 --> 00:18:48.861 line:95%,end
That's great, like,
that your kids are loved.

00:18:48.927 --> 00:18:51.530 line:95%,end
But it's terrible for everyone else.

00:18:52.531 --> 00:18:55.567 line:95%,end
ABBY: Could you quit running
up to the mirror so close?

00:18:56.235 --> 00:18:57.269 line:95%,end
Think!

00:18:57.336 --> 00:19:02.875 line:95%,end
Don't get so close so that you're tumbling
into the stool!

00:19:02.941 --> 00:19:04.710 line:95%,end
I'm not yelling anymore.

00:19:04.776 --> 00:19:07.312 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:19:08.280 --> 00:19:09.448 line:95%,end
Hi. How are you doing?

00:19:09.715 --> 00:19:11.183 line:95%,end
Hello.

00:19:11.250 --> 00:19:12.684 line:95%,end
ABBY: We're headed to Woodbridge, Virginia

00:19:12.751 --> 00:19:14.653 line:95%,end
to attend In10sity Dance.

00:19:14.720 --> 00:19:16.455 line:95%,end
There's hundreds of great studios there,

00:19:16.522 --> 00:19:18.857 line:95%,end
and there's a ton of incredible dancers.

00:19:21.660 --> 00:19:26.365 line:95%,end
I'm excited to go there because two
of my replacement team members,

00:19:26.431 --> 00:19:28.600 line:95%,end
Bella and Kaeli, will be there

00:19:28.667 --> 00:19:32.504 line:95%,end
at In10sity Dance, competing against
the Abby Lee Dance Company.

00:19:33.172 --> 00:19:35.607 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:19:36.475 --> 00:19:39.077 line:95%,end
JILL: Studio Bleu is from Virginia.

00:19:39.244 --> 00:19:42.948 line:95%,end
So we are coming to their hometown.

00:19:43.015 --> 00:19:45.250 line:95%,end
We are invading their turf.

00:19:45.350 --> 00:19:49.655 line:5%,start
And I'm pretty sure they want to beat us
and kick us out of there.

00:19:51.857 --> 00:19:54.126 line:5%,start
Thank you.

00:19:54.193 --> 00:19:57.796 line:5%,start
Watch out for Studio Bleu.
That's all I'm saying.

00:19:57.863 --> 00:20:00.165 line:5%,start
[cheering and applause]

00:20:01.066 --> 00:20:02.467 line:95%,end
Here we go.

00:20:02.534 --> 00:20:04.836 line:95%,end
Come on in, girls.

00:20:04.903 --> 00:20:07.506 line:95%,end
[cheering and applause]

00:20:08.473 --> 00:20:10.576 line:95%,end
You know who the kids
from Studio Bleu are.

00:20:10.976 --> 00:20:16.348 line:95%,end
Bella and Kaeli replaced you at your
studio, the Abby Lee Dance Company,

00:20:16.415 --> 00:20:20.586 line:95%,end
traveling to a competition
wearing my name on their back.

00:20:21.420 --> 00:20:23.488 line:5%,start
Keep your eyes out for them.

00:20:23.655 --> 00:20:25.991 line:5%,start
Make sure you are better than them,

00:20:26.058 --> 00:20:29.461 line:95%,end
stronger, fitter, smarter, sharper.

00:20:29.528 --> 00:20:31.830 line:95%,end
Do all of those things, you'll be fine.

00:20:31.897 --> 00:20:34.800 line:95%,end
Talent prevails.

00:20:34.866 --> 00:20:36.501 line:95%,end
I'm anxious to see their legs and feet,

00:20:36.568 --> 00:20:37.869 line:95%,end
and see how much they've improved

00:20:37.936 --> 00:20:39.671 line:95%,end
with my tricks of the trade.


00:20:39.738 --> 00:20:42.541 line:95%,end
But why would you give another
studio your tricks and trades?

00:20:42.608 --> 00:20:44.009 line:95%,end
ABBY: Because you quit, Kelly.

00:20:44.076 --> 00:20:45.510 line:95%,end
Your kids were sitting at home.

00:20:45.577 --> 00:20:47.479 line:95%,end
They weren't in the studio.

00:20:47.546 --> 00:20:50.182 line:95%,end
Mackenzie, you're my first one up.
All right?

00:20:50.249 --> 00:20:51.483 line:95%,end
You cannot miss a trick.

00:20:51.550 --> 00:20:53.051 line:95%,end
Understood?

00:20:53.118 --> 00:20:55.120 line:95%,end
You have to nail every single trick.

00:20:55.187 --> 00:20:57.089 line:95%,end
If the legs aren't straight
and the feet aren't pointed,

00:20:57.222 --> 00:21:00.158 line:95%,end
you're not gonna win. Go through it.

00:21:00.425 --> 00:21:03.395 line:95%,end
The pressure is on you. You won last week.

00:21:03.462 --> 00:21:06.498 line:95%,end
And I say it every time,
you know, getting to the top is one thing.

00:21:06.565 --> 00:21:08.867 line:95%,end
Staying there is another thing.

00:21:08.934 --> 00:21:11.036 line:95%,end
Mackenzie looks beautiful.

00:21:11.103 --> 00:21:14.106 line:95%,end
That turquoise costume
certainly looks like the beach.

00:21:14.606 --> 00:21:18.677 line:95%,end
But the kid has this look on her face
like she is scared to death.

00:21:18.744 --> 00:21:20.145 line:95%,end
Hey, come on, Mackenzie.

00:21:20.212 --> 00:21:22.581 line:95%,end
Now, remember, the pressure is on.

00:21:22.648 --> 00:21:24.683 line:95%,end
I'm counting on you to win this division.

00:21:24.750 --> 00:21:27.219 line:95%,end
Don't mess it up, kiddo.
Got it?

00:21:27.719 --> 00:21:29.421 line:95%,end
You're not serious enough, Mackenzie.

00:21:29.488 --> 00:21:30.989 line:95%,end
MELISSA: I'm a little
nervous for Mackenzie

00:21:31.056 --> 00:21:32.557 line:95%,end
to have this type of solo.

00:21:32.624 --> 00:21:34.226 line:5%,start
She can be a real cutesy on stage,

00:21:34.293 --> 00:21:37.729 line:5%,start
but this type of emotion
is different for her.

00:21:37.796 --> 00:21:39.064 line:95%,end
Let's go.

00:21:39.131 --> 00:21:42.034 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:21:42.100 --> 00:21:44.836 line:95%,end
[cheering and applause]

00:21:46.938 --> 00:21:48.940 line:5%,start
Abby gave me a harder dance.

00:21:49.007 --> 00:21:51.810 line:95%,end
I'm freaking out that
I'm going to forget my solo.

00:21:52.277 --> 00:21:55.213 line:95%,end
ANNOUNCER: All right. Skipping ahead
just a little bit in your program

00:21:55.280 --> 00:21:58.183 line:95%,end
to entry number nine
in the Mini Solo Division,

00:21:58.250 --> 00:22:01.520 line:95%,end
this is Mackenzie with "Dancing Barefoot."

00:22:01.586 --> 00:22:04.423 line:95%,end
[cheering and applause]

00:22:07.359 --> 00:22:10.195 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:22:16.468 --> 00:22:21.873 line:95%,end
(SINGING) I drove out
to the ocean to catch a breath.

00:22:21.940 --> 00:22:26.778 line:95%,end
Everybody needs to get away.

00:22:26.845 --> 00:22:31.650 line:95%,end
Far from all commotion to clear my head,

00:22:31.717 --> 00:22:36.254 line:95%,end
where I can relax
and take a break.

00:22:36.321 --> 00:22:40.659 line:95%,end
And it's so nice to feel
the sand between my toes,

00:22:40.726 --> 00:22:44.162 line:95%,end
soaking in the sun, letting go.

00:22:44.363 --> 00:22:45.697 line:95%,end
[cheering and applause]

00:22:45.764 --> 00:22:50.669 line:95%,end
(SINGING) And I've got time
to think about important things.

00:22:50.736 --> 00:22:52.571 line:95%,end
ABBY (VOICEOVER): Mackenzie
forgets her dance on stage.

00:22:53.472 --> 00:22:54.639 line:95%,end
Keep going.

00:22:54.706 --> 00:22:56.641 line:95%,end
Keep going. Keep going.

00:22:56.708 --> 00:22:59.945 line:95%,end
There's a one split second
where she goes completely blank.

00:23:00.011 --> 00:23:03.949 line:95%,end
(SINGING) Oh, oh, oh, yeah.

00:23:04.015 --> 00:23:08.487 line:95%,end
Oh, oh, oh, yeah.

00:23:08.787 --> 00:23:11.590 line:95%,end
[cheering and applause]

00:23:12.824 --> 00:23:16.161 line:5%,start
ABBY: The end-- she was early,
so she had to add another chin

00:23:16.228 --> 00:23:19.231 line:95%,end
stand in and ends up finishing
facing the wrong direction.

00:23:19.297 --> 00:23:21.600 line:95%,end
Dumb mistake, Mackenzie. Dumb mistake.

00:23:21.867 --> 00:23:23.835 line:95%,end
- You OK?
- Oh, yeah. I'm fine.

00:23:24.302 --> 00:23:26.438 line:95%,end
- What are you going to do?
- Yeah, you're right.

00:23:26.505 --> 00:23:27.606 line:95%,end
MELISSA: She's not Maddie.

00:23:27.672 --> 00:23:29.541 line:95%,end
- She what?
- MELISSA: She is not Maddie.

00:23:29.608 --> 00:23:31.276 line:95%,end
Hello!

00:23:31.343 --> 00:23:33.145 line:95%,end
Good job, Kenz!

00:23:34.212 --> 00:23:36.314 line:95%,end
Mackenzie, how do you feel like you did?

00:23:39.918 --> 00:23:43.588 line:95%,end
Mackenzie actually danced against eight
and nine-year-olds this week,

00:23:43.655 --> 00:23:47.492 line:95%,end
so I just don't think she was ready
for this type of dance.

00:23:47.559 --> 00:23:50.295 line:95%,end
ABBY: Well, well, well, get on stage
and forget your dance.

00:23:50.362 --> 00:23:51.997 line:95%,end
Looked like a deer in the headlights.

00:23:52.063 --> 00:23:53.665 line:95%,end
You were like this.

00:23:55.033 --> 00:23:57.235 line:95%,end
So, Mackenzie, let's get through
what all you did wrong.

00:23:59.004 --> 00:24:00.372 line:95%,end
You choreographed your own
dance at the end,

00:24:00.439 --> 00:24:01.573 line:95%,end
which I don't really appreciate.

00:24:02.607 --> 00:24:04.209 line:95%,end
You were early on the music.

00:24:04.276 --> 00:24:05.644 line:95%,end
You know, I don't wanna be mean.

00:24:05.710 --> 00:24:06.812 line:95%,end
I don't wanna be nasty.

00:24:06.878 --> 00:24:08.380 line:95%,end
I would have loved to walked in here

00:24:08.447 --> 00:24:11.316 line:95%,end
and had you run and hug me
and be so thrilled

00:24:11.383 --> 00:24:14.252 line:95%,end
with your performance,
but that's not what you do.

00:24:14.319 --> 00:24:17.155 line:95%,end
You were gonna be the overall
high score, eight and under,

00:24:17.222 --> 00:24:19.024 line:95%,end
go out there and do what you did.

00:24:19.090 --> 00:24:20.725 line:95%,end
You went out, you screwed up, you failed.

00:24:20.792 --> 00:24:22.294 line:95%,end
And you know what?

00:24:23.094 --> 00:24:24.663 line:95%,end
She's not ready to do a big girl dance.

00:24:24.729 --> 00:24:28.533 line:95%,end
I don't know what religion you all are,
but I'd start praying.

00:24:28.600 --> 00:24:30.368 line:95%,end
Because that's all we have left.


00:24:35.574 --> 00:24:37.809 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:24:37.876 --> 00:24:39.311 line:5%,start
[cheering and applause]

00:24:39.377 --> 00:24:41.446 line:95%,end
ABBY: Chloe,
when you step out on the stage

00:24:41.546 --> 00:24:43.014 line:95%,end
we should have goose bumps. All right.

00:24:43.081 --> 00:24:44.749 line:95%,end
Ready? Hit play. Let's go.

00:24:44.816 --> 00:24:45.884 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:24:45.951 --> 00:24:47.352 line:95%,end
(SINGING) They say you're doing well.

00:24:47.419 --> 00:24:50.355 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Every time that Chloe has a solo
I'm always trying to be like,

00:24:50.422 --> 00:24:53.625 line:5%,start
"Oh, you know, it's OK."
But I want Chloe to win.

00:24:53.692 --> 00:24:55.126 line:95%,end
I really want her to go out there

00:24:55.193 --> 00:24:59.898 line:95%,end
and I want her to prove that
she is a force to be reckoned with.

00:24:59.965 --> 00:25:02.601 line:95%,end
Girls, if we bump into those kids
that showed up

00:25:02.667 --> 00:25:05.904 line:95%,end
to replace you, you will be nice
and you will say hello,

00:25:05.971 --> 00:25:07.906 line:95%,end
like I have taught you.

00:25:07.973 --> 00:25:10.275 line:95%,end
- OK. Make me proud.
- I will.

00:25:10.342 --> 00:25:11.443 line:95%,end
- Make yourself proud.
- OK.

00:25:11.510 --> 00:25:12.511 line:95%,end
OK.

00:25:12.577 --> 00:25:14.112 line:95%,end
ABBY: The kid that came in
that replaced you,

00:25:14.179 --> 00:25:15.747 line:95%,end
you're now up against.

00:25:15.814 --> 00:25:16.815 line:95%,end
Let's go.

00:25:16.882 --> 00:25:18.149 line:95%,end
Head up, confident.

00:25:19.150 --> 00:25:20.685 line:95%,end
All right. You're gonna be beautiful.
Right?

00:25:21.219 --> 00:25:22.153 line:95%,end
Going to be gorgeous?

00:25:22.220 --> 00:25:24.055 line:95%,end
- ABBY: Hey, ladies.
- Hi, Abby.

00:25:24.122 --> 00:25:25.223 line:95%,end
Abby, how are you.

00:25:25.290 --> 00:25:27.726 line:5%,start
Hi. Girls, this is Bella
and this is Kaeli.

00:25:27.792 --> 00:25:29.628 line:5%,start
- Hi.
- Tell them how old you are.

00:25:30.795 --> 00:25:32.297 line:95%,end
You-- when did--

00:25:32.364 --> 00:25:34.366 line:95%,end
were you not 10 at that audition?

00:25:35.800 --> 00:25:36.968 line:95%,end
Oh, you did. OK.

00:25:37.035 --> 00:25:38.470 line:5%,start
So, Chloe, you're 11.

00:25:38.537 --> 00:25:40.739 line:5%,start
So, all right. Well, best of luck.

00:25:40.839 --> 00:25:41.840 line:95%,end
- She's tall.
- GLORIA: She's confused.

00:25:41.907 --> 00:25:43.008 line:95%,end
You're very tall.

00:25:43.108 --> 00:25:45.977 line:95%,end
Yeah. I'm confused why they had to ask
their moms how old they were.

00:25:46.044 --> 00:25:48.213 line:95%,end
They just had birthdays.
I think they're just a little-

00:25:48.280 --> 00:25:49.514 line:95%,end
Because they compete at different ages.

00:25:49.581 --> 00:25:51.249 line:95%,end
You know the rules.
They compete different ages.

00:25:51.316 --> 00:25:52.617 line:95%,end
ABBY: And January 1st is the age.

00:25:53.818 --> 00:25:55.520 line:95%,end
- I just was wondering.
- They really like making fun of our kids.

00:25:55.587 --> 00:25:56.721 line:95%,end
- [laughs]
- No, no.

00:25:56.788 --> 00:25:58.990 line:95%,end
I was just wondering
because we have problems with people

00:25:59.057 --> 00:26:00.392 line:95%,end
all the time saying fake ages. So--

00:26:00.458 --> 00:26:01.826 line:95%,end
- Oh, no, no, no.
- --that's what we were wondering.

00:26:01.893 --> 00:26:03.695 line:95%,end
We run into these Studio
Bleu dancers in the hall,

00:26:03.762 --> 00:26:05.997 line:95%,end
and Abby's like,
"Oh, tell them how old you are."

00:26:06.064 --> 00:26:07.832 line:95%,end
And the kids are like, how old am I?

00:26:07.899 --> 00:26:10.001 line:95%,end
Like, how do you not know how old you are?

00:26:10.068 --> 00:26:11.269 line:95%,end
- Let's go.
- GLORIA: Good luck, guys.

00:26:11.336 --> 00:26:12.370 line:95%,end
- Good luck.
- You, too.

00:26:12.437 --> 00:26:13.605 line:95%,end
Good luck.

00:26:13.672 --> 00:26:16.408 line:95%,end
You know, we've seen these tricks
before by someone named Cathy.

00:26:16.474 --> 00:26:17.876 line:95%,end
And those people were, like, 27.

00:26:17.943 --> 00:26:19.444 line:95%,end
JILL: That was weird.

00:26:19.511 --> 00:26:20.946 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:26:21.012 --> 00:26:23.848 line:95%,end
[cheering and applause]

00:26:25.917 --> 00:26:28.019 line:95%,end
ANNOUNCER: All right.
Coming to the stage next

00:26:28.086 --> 00:26:32.524 line:95%,end
in the Junior Solo Division,
this is entry number 21, Isabella,

00:26:32.591 --> 00:26:34.626 line:95%,end
with "Over and Over Again."

00:26:34.693 --> 00:26:36.127 line:95%,end
[cheering and applause]

00:26:36.194 --> 00:26:39.030 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:26:46.371 --> 00:26:51.042 line:95%,end
(SINGING) Picture of you
ingrained in my mind,

00:26:51.109 --> 00:26:56.014 line:95%,end
I couldn't help coming undone.

00:26:56.081 --> 00:27:00.986 line:95%,end
If nothing works out in the end,

00:27:01.052 --> 00:27:04.189 line:95%,end
I will still be here

00:27:04.255 --> 00:27:08.893 line:95%,end
over and over and over again.

00:27:08.960 --> 00:27:13.898 line:95%,end
I don't believe you found your happiness.

00:27:13.965 --> 00:27:16.434 line:95%,end
I know what you need

00:27:16.501 --> 00:27:21.740 line:95%,end
and I know it's OK.

00:27:21.906 --> 00:27:24.843 line:95%,end
Ooh.

00:27:24.909 --> 00:27:27.746 line:95%,end
[cheering and applause]

00:27:28.980 --> 00:27:32.183 line:95%,end
ABBY: Bella was not as good
as I thought she was gonna be.

00:27:32.350 --> 00:27:34.386 line:5%,start
She never utilized her space.

00:27:34.452 --> 00:27:37.322 line:95%,end
I think Chloe has a good shot now.

00:27:37.489 --> 00:27:40.525 line:5%,start
ANNOUNCER: All right. Up next
in the Junior Solo Division,

00:27:40.592 --> 00:27:45.730 line:5%,start
this is entry number 22, Kaeli,
with "There's Always Hope."

00:27:45.797 --> 00:27:48.633 line:95%,end
[cheering and applause]

00:27:53.204 --> 00:27:55.707 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:27:55.774 --> 00:27:57.842 line:5%,start
(SINGING) Sometimes a smile,

00:27:58.743 --> 00:28:01.746 line:95%,end
a gentle touch,

00:28:01.846 --> 00:28:04.549 line:95%,end
a soothing word

00:28:06.484 --> 00:28:10.789 line:95%,end
just can't be enough.

00:28:12.023 --> 00:28:18.463 line:95%,end
Into this world we are thrown.

00:28:18.530 --> 00:28:24.636 line:95%,end
And though it seems we're on our own,

00:28:25.970 --> 00:28:32.310 line:95%,end
it's what the moon, the sun,
the sky and stars are for.

00:28:32.377 --> 00:28:38.783 line:95%,end
There's always hope to get you through.

00:28:38.850 --> 00:28:41.853 line:95%,end
Enjoy the ride

00:28:42.687 --> 00:28:49.094 line:95%,end
'cause everything is gonna be all right.

00:28:49.260 --> 00:28:52.797 line:95%,end
[cheering and applause]

00:28:53.398 --> 00:28:55.166 line:95%,end
ABBY: Kaeli is an incredible dancer.


00:28:55.233 --> 00:28:57.202 line:95%,end
She's strong, yet graceful.

00:28:57.268 --> 00:29:02.507 line:5%,start
She has lovely lines, and she can turn
like nobody's business.

00:29:02.574 --> 00:29:04.542 line:5%,start
CHLOE I'm a little bit
nervous before my solo

00:29:04.609 --> 00:29:06.978 line:5%,start
because I don't really like it
when Miss Abby gets back

00:29:07.045 --> 00:29:09.180 line:5%,start
because she gets really loud
and kind of scary.

00:29:09.247 --> 00:29:12.884 line:95%,end
ANNOUNCER: All right. Coming to the stage
next in the Junior Solo Division,

