- So?

00:31:47.438 --> 00:31:49.574 line:95%,end
--instead of just worrying
about your kids? Please.

00:31:49.641 --> 00:31:51.142 line:95%,end
MELISSA: We have
a happy household.

00:31:51.209 --> 00:31:53.144 line:95%,end
Well, your kid
doesn't look very happy to me.

00:31:53.211 --> 00:31:54.345 line:95%,end
- Really?
- Absolutely.

00:31:54.412 --> 00:31:57.148 line:95%,end
ABBY: I think
Sophia Lucia rocked her world.

00:31:57.215 --> 00:31:59.817 line:95%,end
One more thing-- all of you kids,
you need to listen up.

00:31:59.884 --> 00:32:03.454 line:95%,end
If one person really has the dreams
and the passion

00:32:03.521 --> 00:32:04.822 line:95%,end
- to do this for a living--
- Stop.

00:32:04.889 --> 00:32:06.758 line:95%,end
- Keep it together.
- ABBY: --nothing should get in their way.

00:32:06.824 --> 00:32:08.559 line:95%,end
Melissa, listen to what I'm saying.

00:32:08.626 --> 00:32:10.328 line:95%,end
- I'm hearing you.
- Nothing should get in their way--

00:32:10.395 --> 00:32:12.063 line:95%,end
- And I know.
- --not your personal life--

00:32:12.130 --> 00:32:13.464 line:95%,end
I don't have a personal life.

00:32:13.531 --> 00:32:15.800 line:95%,end
ABBY: --not their dad's personal life,
not some other kid.

00:32:15.867 --> 00:32:17.802 line:95%,end
It has nothing to do with that.

00:32:17.869 --> 00:32:19.170 line:95%,end
Maddie needs to focus.

00:32:19.237 --> 00:32:20.638 line:95%,end
- The dance studio--
- MELISSA: I know.

00:32:20.705 --> 00:32:23.875 line:95%,end
--is the place that she thinks of as home.

00:32:23.942 --> 00:32:25.009 line:95%,end
I know that.

00:32:25.076 --> 00:32:26.277 line:95%,end
And you ripped her out of there

00:32:26.344 --> 00:32:28.579 line:95%,end
and let her sit in the parking lot
for 12 hours.

00:32:28.646 --> 00:32:30.081 line:95%,end
I feel sorry for Maddie.

00:32:30.148 --> 00:32:31.683 line:95%,end
She had a good thing going.

00:32:31.749 --> 00:32:35.286 line:95%,end
Melissa, you're doing
your kid an injustice.

00:32:36.621 --> 00:32:39.390 line:95%,end
I am not gonna sit in a dressing room

00:32:39.457 --> 00:32:42.060 line:95%,end
with a bunch of kids and a bunch
of disrespectful mothers.

00:32:42.126 --> 00:32:44.595 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:32:44.662 --> 00:32:47.699 line:5%,start
Abby just took some things
out on Maddie instead of me,

00:32:47.765 --> 00:32:50.335 line:5%,start
and it's just her way of getting to me.

00:32:50.401 --> 00:32:51.936 line:95%,end
Stop. Stop, now.

00:32:52.737 --> 00:32:54.572 line:95%,end
Do you know what? It's OK to cry, though.

00:32:54.639 --> 00:32:55.873 line:95%,end
No, because she has all this makeup on.

00:32:55.940 --> 00:32:57.342 line:95%,end
- It's not OK to cry.
- Well, but I mean, it's OK to let it out.

00:32:57.408 --> 00:32:58.810 line:95%,end
- MELISSA: Because there's no reason.
- JILL: She's upset.

00:32:58.876 --> 00:33:02.213 line:95%,end
That woman just berated her mother,
her father, everybody.

00:33:02.280 --> 00:33:04.282 line:95%,end
You know what? You should be upset, too.

00:33:04.349 --> 00:33:05.883 line:95%,end
And you should have
put a stop to that woman

00:33:05.950 --> 00:33:07.018 line:95%,end
- saying that stuff.
- MELISSA: Do you know what?

00:33:07.085 --> 00:33:08.386 line:95%,end
It is what it is. I have a wonderful life.

00:33:08.453 --> 00:33:09.721 line:95%,end
You let her do that to you.

00:33:09.787 --> 00:33:12.790 line:95%,end
- I'm not gonna upset my child.
- She already upset her for you!


00:33:14.559 --> 00:33:16.828 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:33:18.663 --> 00:33:20.431 line:95%,end
It's obvious
Abby's not coming back in here.

00:33:20.498 --> 00:33:21.899 line:95%,end
- No, obviously.
- No, she's not.

00:33:21.966 --> 00:33:23.868 line:5%,start
We're in the dressing room
getting ready to go on stage,

00:33:23.935 --> 00:33:25.536 line:5%,start
and Abby didn't even
run the dance with them.

00:33:25.603 --> 00:33:26.604 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: OK, girls.

00:33:26.671 --> 00:33:27.905 line:95%,end
If you're dressed, get over here.

00:33:27.972 --> 00:33:29.807 line:95%,end
KELLY: Christi was running
the dance with them.

00:33:29.874 --> 00:33:32.243 line:95%,end
Christi never took
a dance lesson on her life.

00:33:32.310 --> 00:33:34.379 line:95%,end
And Abby expects us
to go out there and get first?

00:33:34.445 --> 00:33:35.813 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Beautiful feet, girls.

00:33:35.880 --> 00:33:38.616 line:5%,start
I might not be a dance teacher,
but I've watched enough dance

00:33:38.683 --> 00:33:41.452 line:5%,start
